sentence: Under Terre 'Blanche, the AWB swore to use violence to preserve minority rule, opposing any concessions offered to the African National Congress - an organisation AWB supporters repeatedly branded as Marxist terrorist s Immediately prior to South Africa's 1994 South African general election, Terre 'Blanche's followers were linked to a number of bombings and assassinations targeting the South African Communist Party; armed AWB commandos participated in the crisis in Bophuthatswana in 1994.
